This is my go-to pizza place. I understand everyone has their preferences, and this is mine. For me, this place has the best crust, hands down. It's the right flavor, texture and thickness. My only gripe is that two toppings cost more than one. I "get" this is a universal pricing standard, but it still makes no sense to me, because the toppings cover the same size of space regardless of how many toppings you get. Pizza topping price should be based on what it is (meat vs. veggie vs. etc), than amount of toppings.

Large-scale slices (surpasses the plate!) on a thin, tender, crunchy, flavourful crust. Being so near to Sal & Carmine's, I hesitated to go here, but am glad to have tried something new. Because it was delicious. My veggie slice ($5) had sliced black  olives, canned mushrooms, chopped broccoli, diced fresh white onion and an extra sprinkle of mozzarella on the top. The sauce is good and tomatoey, which i love, and the cheese a typical NYC pizza blend. Calm environment, thankfully no blaring music, and perfectly bilingual (English-Spanish) staff. Seating is limited to 13 seats at tables, and Cheesy Pizza itself is in one of the beautiful historic buildings that gives the Upper West Side its pleasant character.
